# Bookshelf Apps

Bookshelf Apps is a responsive and interactive web application designed to help users manage their personal book collection. The application features a user-friendly interface that allows you to add new books, mark them as read or unread, and remove books from your list. With local storage integration, your book collection is preserved between sessions, making it an ideal tool for organizing your reading list.

## Features

- **Responsive Layout:**  
  The design adapts to various screen sizes, ensuring an optimal viewing experience on both desktop and mobile devices.

- **Add Books:**  
  Easily add new books to your collection through a modal form with clear input fields.

- **Toggle Book Status:**  
  Mark books as read or unread with a single click, updating their status instantly.

- **Delete Books:**  
  Remove books from your collection using the trash icon for a clutter-free experience.

- **Local Storage Integration:**  
  Book data is saved in your browser's local storage, ensuring your collection is maintained across sessions.

## Technologies Used

- **HTML5**
- **CSS3**
- **JavaScript (ES6)**
- **Local Storage API**
- **Google Fonts**
- **Flaticon** (for icons)

## File Structure

```plaintext
bookshelf-apps-vol.1/
├── index.html              # Main HTML file
├── README.md               # Project documentation
├── assets/
│   └── img/                # Image assets (avatar, book covers, etc.)
├── css/
│   └── style.css           # Main stylesheet
└── js/
    ├── main.js             # Application logic
    └── storage.js          # Local storage handling
```

## Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/muhammadfaizalalkindi/bookshelf-apps-vol.1.git
   ```

2. **Navigate to the project directory:**

   ```bash
   cd bookshelf-apps-vol.1
   ```

3. **Open `index.html` in your preferred web browser.**

## Usage

- **Adding a Book:**  
  Click the "Add" icon to open the modal form, enter the book details (title, author, and publication year), and click "Save" to add the book to your collection.

- **Toggling Book Status:**  
  Use the action buttons on each book to mark it as read or unread.

- **Deleting a Book:**  
  Click the trash icon on any book entry to remove it from your list.

## Customization

- **Styles:**  
  Modify the `css/style.css` file to customize colors, fonts, layouts, and other visual elements to suit your preferences.

- **Scripts:**  
  Update the JavaScript logic in `js/main.js` and `js/storage.js` to adjust behaviors or add new features.

- **Images:**  
  Replace or add images in the `assets/img` directory to reflect your personal style or branding.

